<paragraph id="8B943688FFCFFFD5F9ECFBF7FE5120B2" blockId="5.[151,1437,1004,2039]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCFFFD5F9ECFBF7FEF1209E" bold="true" box="[199,261,1148,1174]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Pupa</emphasis>
(n=2). Total length 
<quantity id="4CD39B6DFFCFFFD5F8D9FBF7FD74209F" box="[498,640,1148,1175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" unit="mm" value="1.85" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.8">1.8–1.9 mm</quantity>
. Cephalothorax greyish brown, abdominal segments greenish brown. Exuviae greyish yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B943688FFCFFFD5F9ECFB4FFC9C21BF" blockId="5.[151,1437,1004,2039]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">
Cephalothorax. Frontal apotome without setae, tubercles and warts. Antepronotum with 2 thin and hair-like median antepronotal setae 85–92 µm long and with 3 lateral antepronotal setae 112–120 µm long. Surface of thorax dorsally smooth. Thoracic horn light brown to brown, 224–232 µm long, broadest at base (30–32 µm), tapering to apex; length horn base 72 µm; horn smooth (
<figureCitation id="13102A0DFFCFFFD5FBAFFABBFCF82142" box="[644,780,1328,1354]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1968,1992]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,309,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-83@6.[162,1426,309,1945]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Pupa of Eukiefferiella claripennis group. 18–19, thoracic horn; 20, tergites I–IV; 21, tergites V–VI; 22, tergite VIII; 23, anal segment; 24, spines and spinules of posterior part of tergites IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592984" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592984/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Figs. 18–19</figureCitation>
). Length horn base/length horn 0.31–0.32. Precorneal setae lengths (in µm): Pc 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5F85AFAEDFE8D217C" attach="left" box="[369,377,1382,1396]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">1</subScript>
40, Pc 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5F8ECFAEDFE3B217C" attach="left" box="[455,463,1382,1396]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">2</subScript>
112–120, Pc 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5FB48FAEDFD9F217C" attach="left" box="[611,619,1382,1396]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">3</subScript>
88–100. Bases of setae arranged in form of triangle. Dorsocentrals hairlike, Dc 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5F9DBFA01FF0C2190" attach="left" box="[240,248,1418,1432]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">1</subScript>
48 µm long, Dc 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5F89AFA01FE4D2190" attach="left" box="[433,441,1418,1432]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">2</subScript>
16 µm long, Dc 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5FB44FA01FD832190" attach="left" box="[623,631,1418,1432]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">3</subScript>
32 µm long, Dc 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5FA06FA01FCC12190" attach="left" box="[813,821,1418,1432]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">4</subScript>
44–48 µm long. Distance between Dc 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5FDCCFA01FB1B2190" attach="left" box="[1255,1263,1418,1432]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">1</subScript>
and Dc 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5FC6CFA01FABB2190" attach="left" box="[1351,1359,1418,1432]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">2</subScript>
12–16 µm; between Dc 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5F87AFA25FEAD21B4" attach="left" box="[337,345,1454,1468]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">2</subScript>
and Dc 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5F89BFA25FE4C21B4" attach="left" box="[432,440,1454,1468]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">3</subScript>
184 µm; between Dc 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5FB81FA25FD4621B4" attach="left" box="[682,690,1454,1468]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">3</subScript>
and Dc 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5FA22FA25FCE521B4" attach="left" box="[777,785,1454,1468]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">4</subScript>
16 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B943688FFCFFFD5F9ECFA4BFAE422F2" blockId="5.[151,1437,1004,2039]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">
Abdomen. Tergite I without shagreen. Tergites II–VIII with weak shagreen of small spinules in anterior third and with 1–2 transverse rows of long needle-like spines, longest of which are 20–28 µm (
<figureCitation id="13102A0DFFCFFFD5FD54FA6FFAFD21F6" box="[1151,1289,1508,1534]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1968,1992]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,309,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-83@6.[162,1426,309,1945]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Pupa of Eukiefferiella claripennis group. 18–19, thoracic horn; 20, tergites I–IV; 21, tergites V–VI; 22, tergite VIII; 23, anal segment; 24, spines and spinules of posterior part of tergites IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592984" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592984/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Figs. 20–22</figureCitation>
). In addition, tergites III– 
<collectionCode id="ED3AAE4DFFCFFFD5F831F982FEDA222B" box="[282,302,1545,1571]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
behind straight spines with row of hooked spines intermittent in middle, apex of which directed anteriorly; their number on these tergites accordingly 13: 15: 14 (
<figureCitation id="13102A0DFFCFFFD5FA65F9A7FC22224E" box="[846,982,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1968,1992]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,309,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-83@6.[162,1426,309,1945]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Pupa of Eukiefferiella claripennis group. 18–19, thoracic horn; 20, tergites I–IV; 21, tergites V–VI; 22, tergite VIII; 23, anal segment; 24, spines and spinules of posterior part of tergites IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592984" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592984/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Figs. 21, 24</figureCitation>
). Shagreen of small spinules in posterior part of sternites 
<collectionCode id="ED3AAE4DFFCFFFD5F879F9DAFE922263" box="[338,358,1617,1643]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
–VII are presented. Segments without PSB and PSA. Segments I–VII with 4 pairs of hair-like lateral setae; length of L 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5F885F90DFE42229C" attach="left" box="[430,438,1670,1684]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">1</subScript>
of these segments (in µm)—24–32, L 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5FA4CF90DFC9B229C" attach="left" box="[871,879,1670,1684]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">2</subScript>
—16–24, L 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5FAD9F90DFC0E229C" attach="left" box="[1010,1018,1670,1684]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">3</subScript>
—16–24, L 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5FD56F90DFB71229C" attach="left" box="[1149,1157,1670,1684]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">4</subScript>
—18–20. Segments VIII with 4 pairs of lateral setae; length of L 
<subScript id="17AF34CDFFCFFFD5FB72F921FD8522B0" attach="left" box="[601,625,1706,1720]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">1–4</subScript>
of this segment (in µm) accordingly—16–32: 16–28: 80–86: 96–112. Anal segment 180–190 µm long, with dorsal and lateral shagreen. Anal lobe with 3 macrosetae 180–200 µm long. Anal segment length/anal macroseta length 0.95–1.11. Female genital sac rounded and short (
<figureCitation id="13102A0DFFCFFFD5FD9BF96BFAF022F2" box="[1200,1284,1760,1786]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–24" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1968,1992]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,309,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-83@6.[162,1426,309,1945]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 18–24. Pupa of Eukiefferiella claripennis group. 18–19, thoracic horn; 20, tergites I–IV; 21, tergites V–VI; 22, tergite VIII; 23, anal segment; 24, spines and spinules of posterior part of tergites IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592984" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592984/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B943688FFCFFFD5F9ECF88FFE6B236E" blockId="5.[151,1437,1004,2039]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCFFFD5F9ECF88FFE572316" bold="true" box="[199,419,1796,1822]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Larva of IV instar</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCFFFD5F880F88FFE2E2316" box="[427,474,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">(n=</emphasis>
2). Total length 
<quantity id="4CD39B6DFFCFFFD5FBBAF88FFCE82317" box="[657,796,1796,1823]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.15" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" unit="mm" value="3.15" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="3.1">3.1–3.2 mm</quantity>
. Head brown to dark brown, antenna light brown or yellowish brown, mandible and mentum brown to dark brown; thoracic segments brownish yellow, abdominal segments brownish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B943688FFCFFFD6F9ECF8FBFD332515" blockId="5.[151,1437,1004,2039]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,151,286]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="379" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">
Head. Labral S-setae simple (
<figureCitation id="13102A0DFFCFFFD5FB24F8FBFD972383" box="[527,611,1904,1931]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–29" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1417,1441]" captionTargetBox="[159,1435,276,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-56@7.[151,1435,273,1393]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25–29. Larva of Eukiefferiella claripennis group. 25, S-setae of labrum; 26, mentum; 27, mandible; 28, antenna; 29, procercus with anal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592986/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Premandible distally with 1 wide apex apical tooth. Antenna with 4 segments; length 1–4 segments (in µm): 49–51: 13–14: 7: 5–6; AR 1.88–1.96; apex of segment 2 with Lauterborn organs ending at 2/3 or base of 3 
<superScript id="7C5E9BC0FFCFFFD5FB22F833FDE323CE" attach="left" box="[521,535,1976,1990]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">rd</superScript>
segment; antennal blade 25 µm long, its apex slightly not reach apex of 4 
<superScript id="7C5E9BC0FFCFFFD5FC72F833FA9223CE" attach="left" box="[1369,1382,1976,1990]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">th</superScript>
segment; one large ring organs in proximal 1/4 of basal segment and one small in distal 1/3 (
<figureCitation id="13102A0DFFCFFFD5FDA5F857FB1723FE" box="[1166,1251,2012,2038]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–29" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1417,1441]" captionTargetBox="[159,1435,276,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-56@7.[151,1435,273,1393]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25–29. Larva of Eukiefferiella claripennis group. 25, S-setae of labrum; 26, mentum; 27, mandible; 28, antenna; 29, procercus with anal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592986/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). Mandible with apical tooth and 3 true inner teeth and one false tooth; seta interna with 3–4 branches; seta subdentalis leaf-shaped, with pointed; inner margin of mandible (mola) with 2–3 short serrations (
<figureCitation id="13102A0DFFCCFFD6FAEDFF30FBEE24DD" box="[966,1050,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–29" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1417,1441]" captionTargetBox="[159,1435,276,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-56@7.[151,1435,273,1393]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25–29. Larva of Eukiefferiella claripennis group. 25, S-setae of labrum; 26, mentum; 27, mandible; 28, antenna; 29, procercus with anal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592986/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="379">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). Mentum with 2 median teeth and 5 pairs of lateral teeth; median tooth in 2.0–2.6 times wider than 1 
<superScript id="7C5E9BC0FFCCFFD6FA51FF54FC7124E5" attach="left" box="[890,901,223,237]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="379">st</superScript>
lateral tooth; ventromental plates large, pointed basally (
<figureCitation id="13102A0DFFCCFFD6F9DDFE88FEBE2516" box="[246,330,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–29" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1417,1441]" captionTargetBox="[159,1435,276,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-56@7.[151,1435,273,1393]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25–29. Larva of Eukiefferiella claripennis group. 25, S-setae of labrum; 26, mentum; 27, mandible; 28, antenna; 29, procercus with anal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592986/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="379">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Maxilla without pecten galearis.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF546600FFCCFFD6F9BCF83BFC0723E4" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592984" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6592984" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592984/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="379" startId="6.[151,264,1968,1992]" targetBox="[162,1425,309,1940]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="8B943688FFCCFFD6F9BCF83BFC0723E4" blockId="6.[151,1436,1968,2029]" pageId="6" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCCFFD6F9BCF83BFEA323C0" bold="true" box="[151,343,1968,1992]" pageId="6" pageNumber="379">FIGURES 18–24.</emphasis>
Pupa of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D0BFFCCFFD6F891F83BFD3423C0" baseAuthorityName="Lundbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[442,704,1968,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Eukiefferiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claripennis">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCCFFD6F891F83BFD3423C0" box="[442,704,1968,1992]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="379">Eukiefferiella claripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. 
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCCFFD6FA38F83BFCAD23C0" bold="true" box="[787,857,1968,1992]" pageId="6" pageNumber="379">18–19,</emphasis>
thoracic horn; 
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCCFFD6FAD7F83BFBE823C0" bold="true" box="[1020,1052,1968,1992]" pageId="6" pageNumber="379">20,</emphasis>
tergites I–IV; 
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCCFFD6FD9CF83BFB2223C0" bold="true" box="[1207,1238,1968,1992]" pageId="6" pageNumber="379">21,</emphasis>
tergites V–VI; 
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCCFFD6FC56F83BFA6823C0" bold="true" box="[1405,1436,1968,1992]" pageId="6" pageNumber="379">22,</emphasis>
tergite VIII; 
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCCFFD6F83DF85FFEC223E4" bold="true" box="[278,310,2004,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="379">23,</emphasis>
anal segment; 
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCCFFD6F8E4F85FFE1A23E4" bold="true" box="[463,494,2004,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="379">24,</emphasis>
spines and spinules of posterior part of tergites IV.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B943688FFCDFFD7F9ECFF1CFE9224F1" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">
Abdomen. Anal tubules 72–88 µm long. Posterior parapods long, 208–216 µm long; posterior parapods length/ anal tubules length 2.3–3.0. Procerci are typical for genus, each bearing 7 long anal setae; lower lateral seta 60–68 µm long (
<figureCitation id="13102A0DFFCDFFD7F82EFF54FEAE24F1" box="[261,346,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–29" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1417,1441]" captionTargetBox="[159,1435,276,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-56@7.[151,1435,273,1393]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25–29. Larva of Eukiefferiella claripennis group. 25, S-setae of labrum; 26, mentum; 27, mandible; 28, antenna; 29, procercus with anal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592986/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF546600FFCDFFD7F9BCFA02FE3021CD" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592986" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6592986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592986/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" startId="7.[151,264,1417,1441]" targetBox="[159,1435,276,1389]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="8B943688FFCDFFD7F9BCFA02FE3021CD" blockId="7.[151,1436,1417,1477]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7F9BCFA02FEA221A9" bold="true" box="[151,342,1417,1441]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">FIGURES 25–29.</emphasis>
Larva of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D0BFFCDFFD7F895FA02FD3621A9" baseAuthorityName="Lundbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[446,706,1417,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Eukiefferiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claripennis">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7F895FA02FD3621A9" box="[446,706,1417,1441]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">Eukiefferiella claripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. 
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7FA38FA02FCC721A9" bold="true" box="[787,819,1417,1441]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">25,</emphasis>
S-setae of labrum; 
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7FD2BFA02FBEB21A9" bold="true" box="[1024,1055,1417,1441]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">26,</emphasis>
mentum; 
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7FDA1FA02FB5D21A9" bold="true" box="[1162,1193,1417,1441]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">27,</emphasis>
mandible; 
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7FC34FA02FACA21A9" bold="true" box="[1311,1342,1417,1441]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">28,</emphasis>
antenna; 
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7F9BCFA26FF4321CD" bold="true" box="[151,183,1453,1477]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">29,</emphasis>
procercus with anal setae.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C3316503FFCDFFD7F9ECFA78FB842295" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B943688FFCDFFD7F9ECFA78FB842295" blockId="7.[151,1437,1523,1802]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7F9ECFA78FECF2205" bold="true" box="[199,315,1523,1549]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">Remarks.</emphasis>
Since the pupae of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D0BFFCDFFD7FB31FA78FCCC2205" baseAuthorityName="Lundbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[538,824,1523,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Eukiefferiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claripennis">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7FB31FA78FCCC2205" box="[538,824,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">Eukiefferiella claripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group were immature and of female, we could not accurately determine their species identity but the larva and pupa are typical representatives of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D0BFFCDFFD7FDFDF99CFAA02239" baseAuthorityName="Lundbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[1238,1364,1559,1585]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Eukiefferiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claripennis">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7FDFDF99CFAA02239" box="[1238,1364,1559,1585]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">claripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and according to identification keys of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B79FFCDFFD7FB75F9B0FCF3225D" author="Schmid, P. E." box="[606,775,1595,1621]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" pagination="1 - 514" refId="ref5943" refString="Schmid, P. E. (1993) A key to the larval Chironomidae and their instars from Austrian Danube region streams and rivers with particular reference to a numerical taxonomic approach. Part I. Diamesinae, Prodiamesinae and Orthocladiinae. Wasser und Abwasser, Supplementband 3 / 93, 1 - 514." type="journal article" year="1993">Schmid (1993)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B79FFCDFFD7FA68F9B0FBF5225D" author="Lehmann, J." box="[835,1025,1595,1621]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" pagination="347 - 405" refId="ref5588" refString="Lehmann, J. (1972) Revision der europaischen Arten (Puppen ♂♂ und Imagines ♂♂) der Gattung Eukiefferiella Thienemann (Diptera: Chironomidae). Beitrage zur Entomologie, 22 (7 / 8), 347 - 405." type="journal article" year="1972">Lehmann (1972)</bibRefCitation>
similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D0BFFCDFFD7FDA9F9B7FEC12271" authority="Goetghebuer. Unfortunately" authorityName="Goetghebuer. Unfortunately" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Eukiefferiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobifera">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7FDA9F9B7FB09225D" box="[1154,1277,1595,1621]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">E. lobifera</emphasis>
Goetghebuer. Unfortunately
</taxonomicName>
, there are no data for 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D0BFFCDFFD7FB08F9EBFD6F2271" box="[547,667,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Eukiefferiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobifera">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7FB08F9EBFD6F2271" box="[547,667,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">E. lobifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the GenBank, and the closest sequence to our 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D0BFFCDFFD7FD92F9EBFAA12271" baseAuthorityName="Lundbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[1209,1365,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Eukiefferiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claripennis">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7FD92F9EBFAA12271" box="[1209,1365,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">E. claripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group is 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D0BFFCDFFD7F99AF90FFE282296" authority="(Lundbeck)" baseAuthorityName="Lundbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[177,476,1667,1694]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Eukiefferiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claripennis">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7F99AF90FFEBA2295" box="[177,334,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">E. claripennis</emphasis>
(Lundbeck)
</taxonomicName>
. For more details see section “Results of DNA barcoding”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3316503FFCDFFD7F9ECF92CFDB92301" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B943688FFCDFFD7F9ECF92CFDB92301" blockId="7.[151,1437,1523,1802]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7F9ECF92CFED822C9" bold="true" box="[199,300,1703,1729]" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">Ecology.</emphasis>
The larvae and pupae of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D0BFFCDFFD7FB6AF92CFCA922C9" baseAuthorityName="Lundbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[577,861,1703,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Eukiefferiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claripennis">
<emphasis id="B95FEA9AFFCDFFD7FB6AF92CFCA922C9" box="[577,861,1703,1729]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">Eukiefferiella claripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in cocoon of black flies pupae were collected on stones with a small amount of algae fouling of a waterfall in a mountain stream at a current speed of 
<quantity id="4CD39B6DFFCDFFD7FC06F940FA7F22ED" box="[1325,1419,1739,1765]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" unit="m" value="0.8" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.6">0.6–1 m</quantity>
/s at an altitude of 
<quantity id="4CD39B6DFFCDFFD7F866F964FE562302" box="[333,418,1775,1802]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.218" pageId="7" pageNumber="380" unit="m" value="2218.0">2218 m</quantity>
a.s.l. (
<figureCitation id="13102A0DFFCDFFD7F8C7F964FDB42301" box="[492,576,1775,1801]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–33" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1382,1406]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,1349]" captionTargetId="figure-94@8.[151,1435,381,1359]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 30–33. Localities of Cardiocladius sp. 1 and Blephariceridae larvae (30–32), Eukiefferiella claripennis group and Simuliidae larvae with pupae (33). 30, Greater Caucasus, Tseyskoye Gorge, Terek River basin, Waterfall on the Shalatsikomdon River (Russia: Republic of North Ossetia–Alania); 31, Greater Caucasus, Skazdon River near the Tseyskoe Gorge (Russia: Republic of North Ossetia–Alania); 32, Greater Caucasus, Avar Koysu River basin, the left tributary of the Dzhurmut River opposite of Choroda Village (Russia: Republic of Dagestan); 33, Greater Caucasus, Avar Koysu River basin, left tributary of the Joahor River, 3 km upstream of its mouth on the Jurmut River (Russia: Republic of Dagestan). (Photos by D.M. Palatov)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592988/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="380">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
